_json.gridTitle: Happy Birthday, Mr. Genius! - Here in the Bonny Glen
_json.description: Kate Douglas Wiggins, author of REBECCA OF SUNNYBROOK FARM, describes her childhood encounter with her favorite author, Charles Dickens:     “Of course,” I explained, conscientiously, “I do skip some of the very dull parts once in a while; not the short dull parts, but the long ones.”    He laughed heartily. “Now, that is something that I hear very little about,” he said. “I distinctly want to learn more about those very dull parts..."
